This paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning algorithm that incorporates the strengths of Neural Programmer-Interpreters (NPI) and AlphaZero. The paper focuses on the development of a new algorithm for learning compositional neural programs with recursive tree search and planning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of natural language processing and computer vision, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of planning and control in robotics, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category.
